tools.description:
Post a video to TikTok by pulling from a URL. Returns publish_id — use get-publish-status to check completion.

NOTE: TikTok has ONE text field ('title' in post_info) which serves as the caption. Include hashtags and @mentions there. There is no separate description field for videos.

Example:
{
  "post_info": {
    "title": "Check this out! #fyp #trending",
    "privacy_level": "PUBLIC_TO_EVERYONE",
    "disable_comment": false
  },
  "source_info": {
    "source": "PULL_FROM_URL",
    "video_url": "https://example.com/video.mp4"
  }
}

Post photos to TikTok (up to 35 images). Returns publish_id — use get-publish-status to check completion.

Example:
{
  "post_info": {
    "title": "My photo carousel",
    "privacy_level": "PUBLIC_TO_EVERYONE"
  },
  "source_info": {
    "source": "PULL_FROM_URL",
    "photo_images": ["https://example.com/img1.jpg", "https://example.com/img2.jpg"],
    "photo_cover_index": 0
  },
  "post_mode": "DIRECT_POST",
  "media_type": "PHOTO"
}

Upload video to TikTok user's inbox for later editing and posting in the TikTok app.

Pull from URL example:
{
  "source_info": {
    "source": "PULL_FROM_URL",
    "video_url": "https://example.com/video.mp4"
  }
}

File upload init example:
{
  "source_info": {
    "source": "FILE_UPLOAD",
    "video_size": 50000000,
    "chunk_size": 10000000,
    "total_chunk_count": 5
  }
}

Query specific TikTok videos by their IDs. Returns detailed video info and metrics. Use this to get analytics for specific videos.

Available fields: id, title, create_time, cover_image_url, share_url, video_description, duration, like_count, comment_count, share_count, view_count, height, width, embed_html, embed_link

Example:
{
  "filters": {
    "video_ids": ["7123456789", "7234567890"]
  }
}
